1 The craft of theſe Empiricks.§. We may obſerve the cunning of thoſe Empiricks, thoſe falſe Phyſicians, who are of no value; they uſe this ſweet welcome word of peace to the people, which is a Catholicon, comprehenſive of all enjoiments (for every want is a kind of war) when they cry peace, and repeat the crambe of peace, peace, and ſing this ſong (or 
   〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
) over and over again;Acts 19.35. they hope, (as Demetrius and his fellow-craftsmen) by crying Great is Diana of the Epheſians, even to a raving and hoarſeneſs, to make the people believe that the image which came down from heaven, was certainly a goddeſs; wih this lullaby of peace, peace, do the Polititians and oppreſſors of a Nation ſeek to quiet the trefe and wayward people, when they cry out of their ailes, and oppreſſions,Iudg. 17.13. as poor Micah did, when the churliſh Danites took away his gods and his Prieſts, yet was he demanded what he ailed ſo to cry after them.

Nothing weakens the credit and Authority of any publick Lawes ſo much as when the Law-givers leaſt obſerve them, or are the firſt that break them: like Phyſicians that preſcribe ſtrict diet to their Patients, but themſelves indulge all manner of Epicuriſme: Here every one is prone to retort;
                  Luke 4.23. 
               Phyſician heal thy ſelf: The beſt things are commonly done by the beſt hands; Religio medici, Conſcience is here required as well as his Science: They will hardly do their Country good, who care not, either to ſerve God, or to ſave their own ſouls.
